{"sectionId":485,"sectionIdLiteral":"485","humanId":"lesson-81","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"ownlineNumber":"Lesson 81"},"annotation":"W-81","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text review-lesson review-2 lesson-81\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"485#0\"><p class=\"p-review-intro\"><span data-sentence-id=\"485#0:1\">Our ideas for review today are:</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"485#1\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">61</span>) <b>I am the light of the world.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"485#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>How holy am I, who have been given the function of lighting up the world!</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me be still before my holiness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>In its calm light let all my conflicts disappear.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>In its peace let me remember Who I am.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"485#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Some specific forms for applying this idea when special difficulties seem to arise might be:</span></p> <p class=\"p-prayer\"><span data-sentence-id=\"485#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let me not obscure the light of the world in me.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let the light of the world shine through this appearance.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>This shadow will vanish before the light.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"485#3\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">3.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#3:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">62</span>) <b>Forgiveness is my function as the light of the world.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"485#3:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>It is through accepting my function that I will see the light in me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#3:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>And in this light will my function stand clear and perfectly unambiguous before my sight.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#3:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>My acceptance does not depend on my recognizing what my function is, for I do not yet understand forgiveness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#3:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Yet I will trust that, in the light, I will see it as it is.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"485#4\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">4.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#4:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Specific forms for using this idea might include:</span></p> <p class=\"p-prayer\"><span data-sentence-id=\"485#4:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let this help me learn what forgiveness means.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#4:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me not separate my function from my will.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"485#4:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>I will not use this for an alien purpose.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Our ideas for review today are: (61) I am the light of the world. How holy am I, who have been given the function of lighting up the world! Let me be still before my holiness. In its calm light let","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 81: Review (61 and 62) | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†81 ‚ÄúReview (61 and 62)‚Äù: Our ideas for review today are: (61) I am the light of the world. How holy am I, who have been‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sec